e(...)`, and the existing build artifacts show JaCoCo method coverage for `generate(...)`.\\n\\nHowever, the dynamic-access report records the call sites as:\\n\\n```text\\ncom.jcraft.jsch.KeyPairRSA.generate(Unknown Source)\\n```\\n\\nThe coverage reporter only marks dynamic-access call sites as covered when the tracked frame includes a source line number. Since this old `jsch:0.1.27` artifact reports `Unknown Source` for these frames, the report cannot correlate the call site to JaCoCo line coverage, even though the method is executed by the test.\\n\\nI did not add another test because there is no alternative supported public API path for `KeyPairRSA.generate(...)`; additional tests would still produce the same `Unknown Source` dynamic-access frames and would not improve the coverage report.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_082619bd3479612a016a1116ee49e881a2826665a6a23fc47f\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 3851, \"output\": 748, \"cacheRead\": 47104, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 51703, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1779504868464, \"responseId\": \"resp_082619bd3479612a016a1116e5934481a2aacfe1514a1445c7\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n[recv] agent_end\n[send] get_state\n[recv] get_state success\n  sessionFile: ../../../../../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge2-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-2236-dd3a1861--/2026-05-23T02-49-46-978Z_019e52bd-20e2-769e-863c-dd3f9c267aa6.jsonl\n  sessionId: 019e52bd-20e2-769e-863c-dd3f9c267aa6\n[send] get_session_stats\n[recv] get_session_stats success\n  tokens: input=123094 output=9711 cacheRead=914944 cacheWrite=0 total=1047749\n\n\n=== human-intervention-logs/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-23T02-44-31-732052Z