:\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering metadata for test classes**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about the dynamic metadata for test classes, and it feels risky to include them in library metadata since that could create unnecessary complications. I realize using test classes for Native Image might not be the best idea. There’s a user-code-filter that includes only library classes, and adding test classes could lead to unwanted metadata generation. I wonder if the metadata really should reflect those test classes, considering the potential consequences. It’s a tricky situation!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_X9JreUxvw9Nw1XoJluHcMWeA|fc_093d359055feef9b016a11056717d481a2bfd38f045e8b3055\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/IdentityFileTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"            receiveEncrypted(SSH_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST);\\n            sendEncrypted(new byte[] {SSH_MSG_USERAUTH_SUCCESS});\\n\", \"newText\": \"            PacketReader signedRequest = new PacketReader(receiveEncrypted(SSH_MSG_USERAUTH_REQUEST), 1);\\n            signedRequest.readString();\\n            signedRequest.readString();\\n            signedRequest.readString();\\n            byte signedFlag = signedRequest.readByte();\\n            signedRequest.readString();\\n            signedRequest.readString();\\n            byte[] signature = signedRequest.readString();\\n            if (signedFlag != 1 || signature.length == 0) {\\n                throw new IOException(\\\"Expected a signed public-key authentication request\\\");\\n            }\\n            sendEncrypted(new byte[] {SSH_MSG_USERAUTH_SUCCESS});\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2852, \"output\": 1361, \"cacheRead\": 83456, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 87669, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"tota